irst systematic criticisms of imperialism published anywhere in the world. In this seminal text, Kotoku condemned global imperialism as the commandeering of politics by national elites and denounced patriotism and militarism as the principal causes of imperialism. In addition to translating Imperialism, Robert Tierney offers an in-depth study of Kotoku’s text and of the early anti-imperialist movement he led. Tierney places Kotoku’s book within the broader context of early twentieth-century debates on the nature and causes of imperialism. He also presents a detailed account of the different stages of the Japanese anti-imperialist movement. Monster of the Twentieth Century constitutes a major contribution to the intellectual history of modern Japan and to the comparative study of critiques of capitalism and colonialism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAnarchistszJapanvBiography. 0aAnti-imperialist movementszJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocialistszJapanvBiography. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Japan.2bisacsh  aanarchy studies.  aanarchy.  aanti imperialist movements japan.  aasian anarchists.  aasian solidarity association.  aasian studies.  aearly 20th century.  aheimenism.  ahistory of japan.  aimperial japan.  aintellectual history of modern japan.  ajapanese anarchists.  ajapanese political history.  ajapanese socialist.  akotoku shosui.  aradical journalism japan.  arusso japanese war.  aturn of the century japan.  aturn of the century japanese radicals.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028634440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096159340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961593423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961593/original  a978-3